            "answer_text": "The Confederate States viewed the Union as a compact between sovereign nations, with each state retaining its sovereignty. The Constitution is, thus, merely a treaty between a group of independent states agreeing to subordinate themselves to an agreed-upon central government. As a treaty between sovereign nations, each nation retained the right to withdraw from the arrangement at any time. ",
